rComments: This professor talks to quietly in class, and he doesn't explain the material. He just stands at the front of the room reading off these lectures notes that he later sends you for you to trifle through. Seems like a useful tool, excluding the fact they're 40 pages on average. Seems like an interesting guy, but his lectures are the death of me.

He is a brilliant philosopher but he is simply not a good professor. He refuses to gather the notes together and has you search out everything from the library. the lectures are mandatory but useless. Nice guy, unfortunate use of his talents

nice guy, horrible teacher. Long readings that are hard to understand and talks too fast in class so it is impossible to take good notes. BORING!!! Tries to make exams easy though, and he gives you prepared essay questions.
